About
The largest stadium in the Netherlands and home to the Ajax football team, it has played host to legendary sporting matches and music concerts.
Duration: 1-2 hours

    Stadium Tour
    Went on the stadium tour during the summer whilst in Amsterdam. Stadium is very easy to get to via public transport and train station is right outside the stadium. Tour guide was very knowledgeable with some great information about Ajax and the stadium. Answered any questions too. Only disappointment on the tour was not being able to see the pitch as it was covered up for a concert but I knew about this in advance. Club shop is also very good and because we booked tickets in advance they gave a discount on items bought in the shop.

kieran
Bristol, UK6 contributions
Great stadium and great stadium tour
Aug 2023 Solo
Great stadium tour would highly recommend to anyone, easily accessible to all as well. With the chance to try on old jerseys within one of the dressing/changing rooms - with shirts from famous players who have played at the Johan Cruijff arena. From Mijatovic (real Madrid 1998) to the Frenkie De Jong Netherlands/Holland jersey from June 2021. Which you can also try on as well (not many stadium tours give you the chance to try on these shirts/jerseys so credit to Ajax. With the club with the great history that it has it was great to see how in-depth they went with the stadium audio tour (a must I believe), with also the chance to sit in both the home and away team benches and to see where which fans sit from the home fans, away fans as well as the hospitality as well.
Written July 20, 2024
